			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Thanks Darc, for the insite on Shadow Knights. As a Dark Elf SK, I'd like to disagree with your comment on SK's not having duel wield. When we reach level 9, we, 'in essence', HAVE duel wield thanks to our pets, giving us this ability at an earlier level than our warrior counterparts! I also wanted to let everyone know what a powerful spell 'Sense the Undead' can be! Look on this spell as a fundraiser! Killing skeletons for their bone chips can be a good source of income as I have sold a stack (20) for an average of 3pp! I was once even paid 40pp for 4 stacks! Along with the fact that Skel's also carry 'pocket change' (even though they have no pockets), and that they often have a weapon that can be sold for a few gp's, this can fund your armor and weapon purposes better than other sources of revenue. Also using 'Find Corpse' spell to assist someone from eternally losing their hard earned equipment can bring some generous donations! So even these simple spells can help you to become a powerful adversary, thanks to the power of money. Use this well and spread darkness and chaos to all those that oppose us!
				</font>
